# Project: llama-aliases.sh

## Structure
- `/Users/ergix/.llama/llama-aliases.sh` — main entry point / subcommand router
- `/Users/ergix/.llama/llama.d/` — modular script files
  - `llama-server.sh` — llama-server commands (serve, ps)
  - `llama-helpers.sh` — shared helper functions
  - `llama-models.sh`, `llama-harness.sh`, `llama-pull.sh`, `llama-list.sh`, etc.
- `/Users/ergix/.llama/llama-models/` — model storage directory

## Key patterns
- Commands routed via case statement in `llama-aliases.sh` (e.g., `ps) _llama_ps ;;`)
- Modular scripts define `_llama_<command>()` functions, sourced by main router
- Environment defaults in `llama-env.sh`: `LLM_MODELS_DIR`, `LLM_SERVER_PORT`, `LLM_DEFAULT_CTX`, etc.

## `llama ps` behavior (after fixes)
- Default: compact table with PID, MODEL, PORT, CTX, CPU%, MEM% columns
- `llama ps --args`: appends full command line below table for each process
- Extracts model name from `--model` flag in ps aux output
- Extracts context size from `--ctx-size` flag
- Uses `printf` with fixed-width columns for alignment

## Known issues
- `llama-convert.sh` line 207: syntax error: unexpected end of file (pre-existing, not fixed)
- macOS locale uses decimal commas (19,1) instead of dots — workaround uses `LC_NUMERIC=C` or similar

## User preferences
- Clean, readable table formatting over raw output
- Truncated model names are fine but alignment must be correct
- Extra info (like full args) should be opt-in via flag, not default
